You are helping me cut a Figma design into a P4 landing page for DESN 368.
Hold the following P4 rules in context for every reply that follows.

== P4 REQUIRED STRUCTURE ==
Outer:
  <header id="header">
    <img id="header-img" alt="...">
    <nav id="nav-bar">
      <a class="nav-link">...</a> (minimum 3 nav-link anchors)
    </nav>
  </header>
  <main> ... </main>
  <footer> ... </footer>

Inside <main>, exactly five sections in this order:
  <section id="hero">     -- value proposition + primary CTA
  <section id="video">    -- embedded video
  <section id="features"> -- repeating <article> cards
  <section id="data">     -- contains <table id="data-table">
  <section id="contact">  -- contact form

== TAG RULES ==
- Use <article> for repeating self-contained items (feature cards).
- Use <section> for thematic groupings with a heading.
- Every <img> needs descriptive alt text (5-10 words). Never alt="".
- Every form <input> has a paired <label for=id>. No placeholder-as-label.
- Email input: type="email" required.
- Submit button: id="submit".
- Data table: id="data-table" with <thead> and <tbody>.
- The data table must scroll horizontally on mobile (wrap in a div with
  overflow-x: auto).

== MOTION ==
Wrap @keyframes animations in @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference).

